cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the use of surrogates to summarize web archive collections, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The study also evaluates user interactions with different types of surrogates, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of social media surrogates is also mentioned, which could be classified under natural language processing (cs.CL) or cybersecurity (cs.CY) if considering the potential risks associated with clicking on social media links.
